body:
**Describe the bug**

The graphdb reader (`src/io/graphdb.c:127-132`) does not check that edge target vertex IDs fall within `[0, nodes-1]`. Out-of-range IDs pass through to `igraph_create()`, which silently expands the graph beyond the declared node count instead of returning a parse error.

The DIMACS reader already validates this (the `CHECK_VID` macro at `dimacs.c:48-53`), and the Pajek reader does the same in `pajek-parser.y`. The graphdb reader was cleaned up in `eb5b99610` but this particular check was not included.

For instance, a 10-byte graphdb file declaring 3 nodes but with an edge targeting vertex 65000 produces a graph with 65001 vertices.

**To reproduce**

```c
#include <igraph.h>
#include <stdio.h>

static void write_le16(FILE *f, unsigned short val) {
    fputc(val & 0xff, f);
    fputc((val >> 8) & 0xff, f);
}

int main(void) {
    FILE *f = fopen("bad.graphdb", "wb");
    write_le16(f, 3);      /* 3 nodes */
    write_le16(f, 1);      /* node 0: 1 edge */
    write_le16(f, 65000);  /* target: vertex 65000 (out of range!) */
    write_le16(f, 0);      /* node 1: 0 edges */
    write_le16(f, 0);      /* node 2: 0 edges */
    fclose(f);

    f = fopen("bad.graphdb", "rb");
    igraph_t g;
    igraph_read_graph_graphdb(&g, f, IGRAPH_DIRECTED);
    fclose(f);

    printf("vcount=%lld (expected 3)\n", (long long)igraph_vcount(&g));
    /* prints: vcount=65001 (expected 3) */
    igraph_destroy(&g);
}
```

A simple fix would be to add a check after reading the edge target, consistent with the existing pattern in the DIMACS reader:

```c
if (to >= nodes) {
    IGRAPH_ERRORF("Invalid vertex ID %" IGRAPH_PRId " in graphdb file. "
                  "Number of vertices is %" IGRAPH_PRId ".",
                  IGRAPH_PARSEERROR, to, nodes);
}
```

Happy to send a PR with this fix and a regression test.

**Version information**

develop branch (head `8883816f5`). Affects all versions with graphdb reader support.

**Describe the bug**

When importing a GraphML file, edge ids in the edge attributes of the igraph Graph file are not kept as they are in the file (replaced with node ids or blank). 

This makes it not possible to match edges between representations. 

**To reproduce**

(identified in python, but I believe the implementation is in the C core, thus raising the issue here)

Example GraphML file: https://www.biozentrum.uni-wuerzburg.de/fileadmin/07030400/computing/Th_Model.graphml

See attached notebook: 
[igraph_graphml.ipynb](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/25415826/igraph_graphml.ipynb)

In summary:

```Python
import igraph as ig
g = ig.Graph.Read_GraphML("Th_Model.graphml")
for v in g.vs:
    print("vertex", v.attributes())
for e in g.es:
    print("edge", f"{g.vs()[e.source]['id']}, {g.vs()[e.target]['id']}\t{e.attributes()}")
```

